	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">If you're an athlete, the Father's Heart Bible™ is for you.</strong> These Bible verses for athletes meet you where the pressure lives — the fear of failure, the identity tied to your performance, the weight of being only as good as your last game. The <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father's Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free on your phone — and it reveals God as a <em>Father</em> from beginning to end. Whether you searched "Bible verses for athletes," "verse before a game," or "does God care about my sport" — the answer starts in one place: your worth was never your stats, your medals, or the scoreboard. You are His beloved, win or lose, before you compete in a single event.`}
	keyTakeaway={`You are not loved because you win, perform, or make the team. You are the Father's beloved child right now — not the highlight-reel version of you. Your identity comes from Him, not from the scoreboard, and He does not keep score against you.`}
	painsHeading={`The pressure athletes carry`}
	painsIntroHtml={`If you feel anxious before you compete, terrified of failing, or like you're only as valuable as your last performance, you are not weak and you are not alone. A whole generation of athletes carries the same weight — and the numbers say it out loud.`}
	painStats={[
