	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Behind every statistic is a real athlete — maybe you. The pre-game nerves that never quite settle. The mistake replaying in your head all night. The sense that one bad performance could erase everything you've worked for. The fear of the day the cheering stops and you don't know who you are without your sport.</p><p>None of this means something is wrong with you. It means you're human, living in a world that ties your value to your performance and your wins — and that's a weight no one was built to carry. There is a Father who sees the real you underneath the jersey, and He has something to say about who you actually are.</p>`}
