	aFatherHeading={`A Father for athletes`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>Here's what almost no one tells you in the middle of a season: the answer to the pressure isn't a better stat line, a bigger win, or finally becoming the athlete you think you're supposed to be. The answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a perfect, holy Father who already loves you, today, win or lose.</p><p>You were not made to earn your worth on the field. You were made to receive it. And the One who made you doesn't grade your performance, rank you against your teammates, or love you more on the days you win. He calls you His beloved child — not the highlight-reel you, not the record-breaking you, but <em>you</em>, right now, in the wins and the losses and the long recovery.</p><p>So before you're a starter, a champion, a captain, a name on a roster — you are His. Your heavenly Father wants to be the steady voice underneath the roar of the crowd, the one who says: I see you, I'm proud of you, and there is nothing you could do — no game you could win or lose — to make Me love you more, or less.</p>`}
