	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for athletes?`, answer: `1 Corinthians 9:24-25 (run for a crown that lasts), Hebrews 12:1-2 (run with endurance), Colossians 3:23-24 (work as for the Lord), Isaiah 40:31 (renew their strength), 2 Timothy 4:7 (I have finished the race), Joshua 1:9 (be strong and courageous, God is with you), and Philippians 4:13 (strength for anything) all speak straight to what athletes carry. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about sports and competition?`, answer: `The Bible uses sport as a picture of the life of faith — Paul compares it to running a race and training for a prize (1 Corinthians 9, Hebrews 12, 2 Timothy 4). It honors discipline and effort, but it points past the trophy to a crown that never fades and an audience of One. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals the God behind those passages as a Father who delights in you, win or lose — read it free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Is there a Bible verse to read before a game?`, answer: `Joshua 1:9 is a favorite before competing: 'Be strong and courageous. Do not be afraid; do not be discouraged, for your Father is with you wherever you go.' Isaiah 40:31 and Philippians 4:13 are also steadying when the nerves hit. You can read or listen to all of them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read — right in the locker room before warmups.` },
